HEADWORD: Primal
<hw>Pri"mal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>primalis</ets>, fr. L. <ets>primus</ets> the first. See
<er>Prime</er>, <pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <def>First; primary; original;
chief.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It hath the <qex>primal</qex> eldest curse upon it.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>primal</qex> duties shine aloft like stars.</q>
<rj><qau>Wordsworth.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Primality</ent>⟦br⟧
